-- Ligety Wins Men’s Giant Slalom; Hoefl-Riesch Takes Women’s Race
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-03-10T15:50:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-10/ligety-wins-men-s-giant-slalom-hoefl-riesch-takes-women-s-race.html
Ted Ligety of the U.S. won today’s
men’s World Cup skiing giant slalom, as  Germany ’s Maria Hoefl-
Riesch took the women’s slalom.  Ligety finished 1.161 seconds ahead of France’s Alexis
Pinturault in Kranjska Gora, Slovenia, with Austrian Marcel
Hirscher third.  Hirscher leads Ligety by 82 points in the giant slalom
standings and also pulled within 55 points of Switzerland’s Beat
Feuz in the overall World Cup race.  Hoefl-Riesch beat Slovakia’s Veronika Zuzulova by one-
hundreth of a second in Are, Sweden, with Canada’s Marie-Michele
Gagnon third. Austria’s Mariles Schild, who’s already clinched
the slalom title, was sixth, while  Lindsey Vonn  of the U.S., who
claimed her fourth overall title yesterday, didn’t complete her
second run.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  